  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving circular farming and agriculture in the Democratic People&apos;s Republic of Korea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project, as per the request of the Permanent Mission of DPRK and following the previous cooperation between UNIDO and DPRK, originates from a feasibility study on Circular Farming and Agriculture conducted by UNIDO and DPRK in January 2020 to conduct a scoping and programming work as well as provide technical expertise and support. The overarching objectives are to promote in DPRK circular farming system which aligns with international best practice for integrated eco-farming of crops and animals; as well as produces energy from waste emanating from the system (closed loop production system). Proper study, design and implementation of this system is expected to lead to sustainable agriculture (which balances the triple bottom-line imperatives of environment, economy and society) and improved livelihood of farmers, a model that could be escalated nationally and internationally.</narrative>
  </description>
